This paper deals with the problem of hyper-parameter tuning in machine learning, which falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses experimental design, which can be categorized under "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Systems and Control" (cs.SY). The use of Bayesian optimization and Gaussian mixture models suggests a focus on "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS) and "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE).
